Natural ecosystems and protected species are at risk during the coronavirus crisis. In many countries, environmental protection workers at national parks and nature reserves are required to stay at home in lockdown, leaving these areas unmonitored. Their absence has resulted in a rise in illegal deforestation, fishing, and wildlife huntingâ. The stoppage of ecotourism activity has also left natural ecosystems at risk of âillegal harvesting and encroachmentâ. As ecotourism is often a major economic mainstay in many destinations, rising unemployment caused by the crisis may lead many households to harvest resources from fragile ecosystems unsustainably to seek alternative means to make a living. Many of the environmental challenges caused by the coronavirus crisis will gradually resolve on their own once the crisis comes to an end and previous levels of economic activity resume.
The stoppage of ecotourism activity has also left natural ecosystems at risk of âillegal harvesting and encroachmentâ.

River Ganges 
The River Ganges is one of Indiaâs most important rivers. Filled with industrial, sewage, agricultural, and tourism waste, the Ganges is also one of the world's most polluted rivers. However, just four weeks since the start of the complete shutdown, reports about how clean the waters of the Ganges had become started to emerge. In some places, the waters had even become potable again for the first time in two decades. 
Beaches asâ turtleâ havens
 Around the world, as tourists have retreated from beaches, turtles have been returning to hatch on the beaches. Most species of turtles are endangered, as tourism often disturbs fragile breeding grounds on prime beach locations. Since the coronavirus outbreak, the beaches became silent again, providing friendly places for turtles to lay their eggs. 
Horseshoe Crabâ recovery in the Chesapeake Bay
Chesapeake Bay, located in the Eastern United States, is one of the largest brackish water bays in the world. Each April and May, an incredible spawning of hundreds of thousands of Horseshoe Crabs â a relic species of the dinosaur age â take place on the shores of the Chesapeake Bay at the full moon. This coincides with the  9000-mile migration from Brazil to the Arctic of the Red Knots birds, who feast on the eggs of the spawning Horseshoe Crabs. For years, overfishing for the valuable blue blood of the Horseshoe Crab, which is essential for the pharmaceutical industry, has led to their numbers plummeting and resulted in the decline of the populations of Red Knots too. 
Endangeredâ ottersâ return to lakes in Malaysia
 The endangered otters had been in decline in Malaysia for many years. However, during the COVID-19 lockdown(also known as Movement Control Order in Malaysia), otters were spotted in the usually crowded Putrajaya Lake and several other lakes inland within Malaysia. This has been in line with the clearer air and other environmental improvements seen in Malaysia during the MCO. Otter is a protected species under Malaysian Law and had been hunted or displaced by human activities before the COVID-19 outbreak. 
Break forâ fishâ with docked fishing fleets worldwide
 With COVID-19, most coastal fleets have stayed docked in port, as can be seen from satellite tracking of fishing activity. Coastal fisheries were affected the most. Compared with the same period last year, coastal fishing activities from China, Spain, Italy, and France have decreased by 50-75%. Industrial fishing activity â where vessels often stay at sea for months on end, relying on a system of âmother shipsâ or transshipments â was less affected and activity was only down 10% compared to the same period last year. 
All ocean life benefit from quieter oceans 
â In the Middle East a pod of 2000â dolphinsâ emerged off the coast of Fujairah in the UAE. 
â Similarly,â rays, dolphins, and sharksâ have been seen off the coast of Dubai and the other Gulf States. 
â A superpod of 350 Sperm âWhales âoff the coast of Sri Lanka. 
â Off the coast of Thailand, there have been more sightings of the usually shy and endangered Dugongsâ. 
â Off the coast of California, unimaginable footage has emerged of a âwhaleâ playing with an off-duty fireman in Monterey Bay.

Air travel has also taken a major hit, thanks to orders to shelter in place around the globe. As a result, greenhouse gas emissions will predictably decline. Airplane emissions of carbon dioxide reached over 900 million tons in 2018 and are predicted to triple by 2050, according to the United Nationsâ International Civil Aviation Organization (ICAO). Even though aircraft designs are becoming more and more fuel-efficient, the projected increase in demand for international and long-range travel outweighs the increase in fuel-usage efficiency. Due to COVID-19 ravaging across the globe, current fuel consumption has dropped drastically. In the first three months of 2020, 67 million fewer passengers flew in Europe compared to the same period last year. In the United States, domestic air traffic fell by about 40 percentâ. While this trend will reduce pollutant emission, it would also cause mass layoffs and voluntary unpaid leaves.
Nonetheless, even as airlines are becoming more fuel-efficient, the increase in demand was projected to outweigh the gains

Imagination is Power
        	This story begins in a long time ago, in a land far far away. This is a land filled with magical people. Itâs not that everyone has a wand or anything, but every citizen has a gift of his or her own. This gift was given to them from the moment they were born. However it is not until the year they turn 15 when the guardian angel tells them what their gift is and how to master it.
        	There was a boy (Andy) who was the youngest among his classmates. Maybe because of the filthy clothes he wore on his skinny body, or the funny looking glasses hanging on his nose that made him the main target for the bullies in his school. Every time he was bullied, he would (climb to the top of a mountain to)(maybe) meditate. Or not actually to meditate but to imagine. He imagined he could have friends, be the most popular student in class,and to at least be friends with his crush-
suddenly his crush(main actress named Jessica) walked up to him and asked him what he was doing. Just by that, they became friends. Things got better and better as time went by. Jessica being one of the most popular girl in school, told the bullies not to ever bully Andy again.  Andy started to enjoy his life at school made new friends and a bestie named Kevin.
        	It was the day when Andy gained the courage to confess Jessica, but when he finally found her, she was holding hands (or kissing but that may be awkward) with Kevin. Andy was so depressed that he burst out of the corridor and dashed into a dark room. The room was incredibly large it may seem more like a chamber than a room. But he didnât realize it as he ran to a corner and sat there sobbing. After a long period of time, when Andy was better and was ready to go out, someone came in. A man wearing an intimidating mask came in talking to himself saying that he had gotten the map for the infinite stone. Of course, Andy told Jessica and Kevin about this (completely forgotten about what happened before). They assumed that it was one of Andyâs imagination and ignored it.
        	Until the day, when they went to the fairy for their gifts, the fairy told Jess that her gift was âCourageâ and should go on a quest to find the infinity stone did Andyâs friends believe him. After weeks of finding, Kevin found a way to the stone. After a number of tasks(or just climbing)(and worrying about the masked man), they finally was in front of the cave of infinity(only one person can fit). However, Jess twisted her ankle so Andy volunteered to go get it for her. However, Andy was amazed by the power the stone gave him. When he decided he would take the stone for his own, Kevin came in, helding a mask, the mask, in his hand and said that he was the masked man all along and that he had killed Jessica on the way in (on his other hand holding a dagger with blood)(Kevinâs gift was âintelligenceâ lying to his friends without them knowing). Kevin charged to kill Andy, but Andy having the infinity stone made Kevin stab himself instead. Andy rushed out of the cave only to see his dying crush lying on the ground. He was so repent of what he did. As he fell to the ground remembering what his gift was(imagine things and sometimes making the imagination true). He began his imagination. He imagined that he was Jessâ boyfriend all along(from the confessing part to the tasks part), and he had helped her get to the stone himself and imagined her and Kevin of not being dead.
        	Andy opened his eyes expecting that everything has gotten back to normal. To his surprise the corpse of jess was still laying still in his hands. The fairy appeared. Saying. There are things you cannot change, there are things that will not go as well as you planned. Your imagination may help you improve your future but it could never change the past. Sometimes you just have to let it go and remember to be true to your heart, be the boy your parents want you to be when they send you in the iep program. Andy was confused at first but thenâ¦.
        	Andy woke up. He found out that he was in his own bed. From outside the door came a voice telling him to wake up now or he will be late for the wego school bus.That is when he realized it was all a bad dream.
The End
